description.narrative:
Provide needed investment in a priority fragile and conflict affected country:  Iraqs economic growth has been stunted by years of political instability and violence. The limited private investment that has reached the country has been concentrated in the real estate and oil sectors, which account for over 75% of total FDI. This investment will contribute to the strengthening and diversification of the Iraqi economy. 

Expand telecommunications services: With a population of 30 million and per capita income of US$3,000 (PPP terms), Iraq is one of the poorest countries in the Middle East. Although the telecommunications sector has rebounded in recent years, access to telecommunications continues to be limited and service quality is poor. By extending its network, Zain Iraq will be able to offer communications to remote and underserved populations that previously have not had access to telecommunications services;
Support the delivery of social services: The 2003 conflict as well as ongoing security challenges have interrupted the delivery of basic services in Iraq.  In environments such as these, telecommunications operators are pioneering the delivery of social services such as banking, education and healthcare using the mobile platform. This Project will enable Zain Iraq to expand on these initiatives, and thus extend basic services to a larger share of the population.
